01:49.708 --> 01:52.210
Harvey is going to love
this magic gondola ride.

01:52.278 --> 01:54.379
I just hope he didn't get me
the same thing.

01:54.447 --> 01:56.214
(bird chirping)

01:56.282 --> 02:00.085
Ah, the first robin of spring.

02:00.152 --> 02:01.119
That's him.

02:01.186 --> 02:02.587
Devil bird.

02:02.654 --> 02:04.121
That miserable little magpie

02:04.189 --> 02:05.223
has been keeping me up

02:05.290 --> 02:07.525
all night
with his incessant chirping.

02:07.592 --> 02:08.759
He must be stopped.

02:08.828 --> 02:10.061
Oh, if only we
had a house cat

02:10.095 --> 02:11.762
to rid us of this
terrible blight.

02:11.830 --> 02:12.998
You're right.

02:13.065 --> 02:15.900
What kind of feline am I?

02:15.968 --> 02:18.102
(as Schwarzenegger):
Bird, prepare to be Salem-ated.

02:18.170 --> 02:20.071
Sabrina, what if he
actually catches

02:20.139 --> 02:21.840
that poor defenseless bird?

02:21.907 --> 02:22.840
SALEM:
Little help?

02:22.908 --> 02:23.942
Oh, boy.

02:24.009 --> 02:25.076
Never mind.

02:26.611 --> 02:28.646
(groaning)

02:28.713 --> 02:30.181
Whoo.

02:30.249 --> 02:33.251
I think we should downplay
Valentine's Day around Hilda.

02:33.318 --> 02:34.519
I just felt so sorry

02:34.586 --> 02:35.887
for her this morning.

02:35.955 --> 02:38.422
I mean, you have Harvey,
and I have Willard.

02:38.490 --> 02:41.359
Well, if it's any consolation,
I think she feels worse for you.

02:41.426 --> 02:42.527
She's been so depressed

02:42.528 --> 02:45.096
ever since she had to send
Daniel Boone back.

02:45.164 --> 02:48.199
Now she just spends her days
moping around the attic.

02:48.267 --> 02:51.469
So you really never had an
Indian friend named Mingo?

02:51.536 --> 02:53.471
No, ma'am, there isn't much
companionship in the wild.

02:53.539 --> 02:57.508
Believe me, when a tree falls
in the forest, I hear it.

02:57.576 --> 03:00.111
Well, you can stay here
as long as you like--

03:00.179 --> 03:01.980
I mean, until we get
bored of each other

03:02.047 --> 03:04.015
or my sister finds out.

03:04.083 --> 03:05.082
Look at this.

03:05.150 --> 03:07.819
It's just addressed
"To My Valentine."

03:07.886 --> 03:09.487
And it's not signed.

03:09.555 --> 03:11.690
"Dear Valentine, I wish
I could express in words

03:11.757 --> 03:13.692
how truly special
you are to me."

03:13.759 --> 03:16.160
Harvey can be so sweet.

03:16.228 --> 03:17.895
Sabrina,
clearly this was written

03:17.963 --> 03:21.432
by a worldly, sophisticated,
mature man.

03:21.500 --> 03:23.234
My monkey.

03:23.302 --> 03:25.870
Come on, this has lovesick
adolescent written all over it.

03:25.938 --> 03:27.171
(knocks on door)

03:27.239 --> 03:29.507
Hey, good morning. Thought
I could walk you to work.

03:29.574 --> 03:30.909
Thank you for
my valentine.

03:30.976 --> 03:32.009
Valentine?

03:32.077 --> 03:33.811
I didn't send you
a valentine.

03:33.846 --> 03:36.848
But I did get you, uh...
this stick of gum.

03:36.915 --> 03:39.484
It's sugarless,
and, uh, this watch.

03:39.551 --> 03:41.719
Okay, before I have to thank
you for your high-tops,

03:41.787 --> 03:43.220
Valentine's Day
isn't until Monday.

03:43.288 --> 03:44.656
I knew that.

03:44.723 --> 03:46.257
Uh, I can't walk you to work

03:46.324 --> 03:47.992
'cause I have
to go to the mall

03:48.060 --> 03:51.629
and... get them to gift wrap
the stuff I already got you.

03:51.697 --> 03:53.531
Oh, monkey, I'm so
sorry you're sick.

03:53.599 --> 03:55.500
Drink fluids.

03:55.567 --> 03:57.368
I love you.

03:57.436 --> 04:01.539
He's got a cold, and he's got
no idea it's Valentine's Day.

04:01.606 --> 04:02.741
Well, if Harvey
didn't send it

04:02.808 --> 04:04.108
and Mr. Kraft
didn't send it,

04:04.176 --> 04:06.911
then... it must have
been sent for Aunt Hilda.

04:06.979 --> 04:08.146
Sabrina, you're right.

04:08.213 --> 04:10.347
And it couldn't have come
at a better time.

04:10.415 --> 04:11.849
(whistling)
Do we still have

04:11.917 --> 04:13.518
any of that venison left?

04:13.586 --> 04:16.487
It's a wonder she can
get up in the morning.

04:16.555 --> 04:18.822
Aunt Hilda, look what came
for you in the mail--

04:18.891 --> 04:21.024
an anonymous valentine
from some secret admirer.

04:21.093 --> 04:22.494
Couldn't be for me.

04:22.561 --> 04:24.162
I'll be up in the attic

04:24.229 --> 04:26.965
making sure our wiring
is up to code.

04:26.965 --> 04:30.534
She's breaking my heart.

04:30.603 --> 04:32.503
Relax, I don't want
your powder pouch

04:32.571 --> 04:33.938
or your "chaw of tobacky."

04:34.006 --> 04:35.907
Valentine's Day
isn't until Monday.

04:35.974 --> 04:38.642
Good, 'cause I'm fixin'
to make you a nice fur cap.

04:38.710 --> 04:40.879
If I could just trap
that pesky black varmint

04:40.946 --> 04:42.447
I see scurrying around here.

04:42.514 --> 04:43.814
That's our family pet.

04:43.882 --> 04:45.783
So if you're thinking
of trapping him...

04:45.851 --> 04:48.219
he loves peanut butter.

04:48.287 --> 04:49.320
(chirping)

04:49.388 --> 04:51.155
Shut up, shut up, shut up!

04:51.223 --> 04:53.591
Why must you keep tormenting me?

04:53.659 --> 04:54.492
I've got bad news.

04:54.560 --> 04:56.294
That insane voice
in your head is you.

04:56.362 --> 04:57.495
No, it's that bird.

04:57.563 --> 04:59.164
I know he's taunting me.

04:59.231 --> 05:02.033
If I could just understand
what he's saying.

05:03.502 --> 05:05.670
Hey, everybody, look
at this pathetic tub-o-fur

05:05.738 --> 05:08.440
who couldn't catch a bird
if his life depended on it.

05:08.507 --> 05:11.409
Now it's personal.

05:11.476 --> 05:13.578
One double vanilla latte
with a dash of cinnamon

05:13.646 --> 05:14.779
to kick it up a notch.

05:14.847 --> 05:15.780
Thanks, but...

05:15.847 --> 05:18.082
who needs cinnamon
when I got your smile?

05:21.252 --> 05:23.020
The number one perk
about this job--

05:23.088 --> 05:25.055
besides the low pay
and bad hours--

05:25.123 --> 05:27.858
is getting to flirt with
every cute guy in Westbridge.

05:27.926 --> 05:30.394
Hey, an anonymous valentine
showed up at our house today.

05:30.462 --> 05:32.030
Maybe it's
from one of these guys.

05:32.097 --> 05:34.431
You got an
anonymous valentine.

05:34.499 --> 05:36.601
The girl with the
devoted boyfriend

05:36.668 --> 05:38.169
also gets the
secret admirer?

05:38.237 --> 05:39.637
And they say
life isn't fair.

05:39.705 --> 05:42.740
We're out of
fat-free muffins

05:42.808 --> 05:45.610
so push these calcium-rich
cheese Danish.

05:45.677 --> 05:48.145
So, any big plans
for Valentine's Day?

05:48.213 --> 05:51.515
A gondola-riffic night out
with Harvey-- nothing special.

05:52.450 --> 05:53.418
Though it appears

05:53.486 --> 05:56.187
our Sabrina may have
a secret admirer.

05:56.255 --> 05:57.222
Oh, really.

05:57.289 --> 05:58.556
Any ideas?

05:58.624 --> 06:01.493
Like any secret admirer,
he prefers to remain anonymous.

06:03.795 --> 06:04.796
(hiccups)

06:06.198 --> 06:07.565
Are you okay?

06:07.632 --> 06:11.368
Oh! Got to stop wolfing
down those pickled eggs.

06:13.438 --> 06:16.074
Cute and she eats
like a trucker.

06:16.141 --> 06:18.542
Apparently, if you're
in love with someone

06:18.610 --> 06:22.113
even their involuntary muscle
contractions are endearing.

06:22.181 --> 06:24.348
There are lots of ways
of trapping a bird.

06:24.416 --> 06:27.518
The simplest is the box-
and-the-piece-of-string method.

06:27.585 --> 06:28.753
(chuckling)

06:28.821 --> 06:31.623
What animal would be slow enough
to get caught...

06:31.690 --> 06:34.258
Whoa! What happened?

06:34.326 --> 06:35.793
I don't understand
why you aren't

06:35.861 --> 06:38.296
more interested
in who sent you
this valentine.

06:38.364 --> 06:40.064
Because for every handsome,
debonair man

06:40.132 --> 06:41.432
that might have sent it,

06:41.500 --> 06:43.667
there's a guy named Chester
with a plate in his head.

06:43.735 --> 06:45.770
I just want to see you happy.

06:45.837 --> 06:47.137
I couldn't be happier.

06:47.205 --> 06:49.006
Now, if you'll excuse me,

06:49.074 --> 06:50.308
I'll be up in the attic.

06:50.375 --> 06:51.876
While you're up there

06:51.944 --> 06:53.945
could you grab me
some buckshot, honey bee?

06:54.012 --> 06:55.780
I want to show Salem here
how to load a musket.

06:55.847 --> 06:59.684
I think honey bee's
got some 'splaining to do.

06:59.751 --> 07:01.920
What does "stay in
the attic" mean to you?

07:01.987 --> 07:03.054
Don't worry-- your cat said

07:03.122 --> 07:04.956
he'd warn me
at the first sign of trouble.

07:05.023 --> 07:06.924
Watch out. Here they come.

07:06.991 --> 07:08.826
Hilda, I can't believe...

07:08.893 --> 07:10.695
Hold on, you wouldn't want
to hurt a person who...

07:10.763 --> 07:14.298
someone apparently
loves very much.

07:14.366 --> 07:15.900
Hey.

07:15.968 --> 07:18.269
Hope you're not still mad
about Valentine's Day

07:18.337 --> 07:22.006
but I brought you
a chocolate kiss and a real one.

07:22.073 --> 07:23.541
(hiccups)

07:23.609 --> 07:26.877
Number one cure for hiccups--
spoonful of sugar.

07:26.945 --> 07:28.880
Yes, but only the special
sugar we have at home.

07:28.981 --> 07:30.248
See ya.

07:32.785 --> 07:34.051
She's still mad.

07:34.119 --> 07:37.755
This weekend,
I'm buying myself a calendar.

07:37.823 --> 07:40.091
Even though our paths only
crossed for an instant,

07:40.159 --> 07:42.893
you'll always have a
special place in my heart.

07:42.961 --> 07:44.729
Ditto.

07:48.801 --> 07:52.103
Boy, I'm really going
to miss him.

07:52.170 --> 07:53.437
And now I'm done.

07:53.505 --> 07:55.072
Do you want to get pedicures?

07:55.140 --> 07:56.807
You know, you should
never have broken

07:56.875 --> 07:57.875
the Other Realm rules

07:57.943 --> 08:00.077
and kept him up in the attic
all that time.

08:00.145 --> 08:01.846
The basement was moldy.

08:01.913 --> 08:04.214
And now you're all alone.

08:04.282 --> 08:06.116
Oh, you poor dear.

08:06.184 --> 08:07.084
Interesting.

08:07.152 --> 08:09.587
You were less irritating
when you were angry.

08:09.655 --> 08:11.923
You are so brave.

08:11.990 --> 08:14.525
I am not going to rest

08:14.593 --> 08:17.061
until I find out
who sent you this valentine.

08:17.129 --> 08:18.462
How are you going
to do that?

08:18.530 --> 08:20.331
Interview every guy
I've ever dated?

08:21.399 --> 08:23.101
Excuse me.

08:25.037 --> 08:26.470
All right, all right.

08:26.538 --> 08:29.774
All the A's over
by the cash register, please,

08:29.842 --> 08:31.843
and have your
handwriting samples out

08:31.910 --> 08:33.244
and ready for analysis.

08:33.312 --> 08:36.179
I know this isn't the
point of this exercise

08:36.246 --> 08:39.082
but some of these guys
owe me money, too.

08:39.150 --> 08:39.984
It's not fair.

08:40.051 --> 08:41.251
I haven't used my magic.

08:41.318 --> 08:42.419
I haven't done a spell.

08:42.453 --> 08:44.022
I haven't disobeyed my aunts

08:44.089 --> 08:46.624
and yet, I'm hiccuping
sparkly pink hearts.

08:46.691 --> 08:48.959
Yep, life's
just one big adventure.

08:49.027 --> 08:52.963
And speaking of adventure,
come with me deep into the bush

08:53.031 --> 08:55.633
as we stalk
the elusive dickey bird.

08:55.700 --> 08:57.802
Sometimes I think you actually
work at being annoying.

08:57.869 --> 08:59.670
No, not really.

09:00.405 --> 09:02.673
So that was a dead end,

09:02.741 --> 09:05.143
but I think, if
we systematically
retrace your steps

09:05.210 --> 09:06.610
over the last
three months...

09:06.678 --> 09:09.614
Sometimes I think you actually
work at being annoying.

09:09.681 --> 09:11.382
No, not really.

09:13.718 --> 09:15.519
Where have you been?

09:15.654 --> 09:17.087
Sweaty brow,
panicked expression,

09:17.155 --> 09:18.856
frantically looking
through the magic book--

09:18.924 --> 09:20.691
just what every parent
wants to come home to.

09:20.759 --> 09:21.392
Look.

09:21.460 --> 09:23.660
(hiccups)

09:23.728 --> 09:25.530
Sabrina, this looks serious.

09:25.530 --> 09:27.331
What's the matter with you?

09:27.399 --> 09:28.732
It's a very funny story.

09:28.800 --> 09:29.933
I don't know!

09:30.001 --> 09:32.070
You put Sabrina to bed;
I'll call Cupid.

09:32.137 --> 09:33.437
Cupid?
Cupid.

09:33.505 --> 09:34.939
He handles all
heart-related matters--

09:34.973 --> 09:36.474
literal or figurative.

09:36.542 --> 09:38.609
And who gives the second
opinion, the Easter bunny?

09:41.246 --> 09:42.847
What's with
the getup, bwana?

09:42.915 --> 09:45.049
I'm going big-game hunting.

09:45.116 --> 09:47.251
Looks like a big game
doodied on your hat.

09:47.319 --> 09:50.621
Yeah? Well, it happened
to Hemingway all the time.

09:50.689 --> 09:53.558
Wow. Your heart's
beating louder
(heart beating loudly)

09:53.625 --> 09:56.694
than the bass on a
Deadhead's boom box.

09:56.762 --> 09:57.661
Oh, I can't imagine why.

09:57.729 --> 09:58.996
My anxiety level is

09:59.064 --> 10:00.865
in "there aren't enough
lifeboats" territory.

10:00.932 --> 10:03.467
Finally.
Where's Cupid?

10:03.534 --> 10:05.335
Well, Cupid's a little backed up
with Valentine's Day,

10:05.403 --> 10:07.371
so he had to send his assistant.

10:07.438 --> 10:08.472
Where's the patient?

10:08.540 --> 10:09.974
Roland?

10:10.042 --> 10:11.408
Okay, you've scared me,

10:11.476 --> 10:13.111
but I've still
got the hiccups.

10:13.178 --> 10:14.545
You know,
some people collect stamps.

10:14.612 --> 10:16.480
Other people
seem to collect jobs.

10:16.548 --> 10:19.350
Helping people find love
is my true calling.

10:19.417 --> 10:21.418
Plus, I already had the outfit.

10:21.486 --> 10:23.454
So, what seems
to be the problem?

10:23.521 --> 10:24.955
Well, my heart
is racing,

10:25.023 --> 10:27.591
I'm hiccuping valentines,
and you're in my bedroom.

10:27.659 --> 10:29.594
How can you make
all three go away?

10:29.661 --> 10:31.328
Oh, Sabrina, calm down.

10:31.396 --> 10:32.362
I'm sure
Roland can help.

10:32.398 --> 10:34.097
Sorry. I meant that
to sound sincere.

10:35.367 --> 10:36.467
(chirping)

10:36.535 --> 10:39.136
Now you mock me
in front of my family?

10:39.204 --> 10:40.170
Why you...

10:40.973 --> 10:42.173
Salem, no!

10:42.241 --> 10:43.574
(grunting, thud)

10:43.641 --> 10:46.143
My spleen!

10:46.211 --> 10:49.280
Oh.
I'm okay!

10:49.348 --> 10:50.815
Uh, he's got nine lives,
people, and I'm working on

10:50.882 --> 10:52.516
the only one I
got over here.

10:52.584 --> 10:54.752
Well, I really
won't know anything

10:54.819 --> 10:56.053
until I open her up.

10:56.121 --> 10:56.954
Open me up?

10:57.022 --> 10:58.789
I may be
the only one concerned here,

10:58.857 --> 11:01.158
but he's not a real doctor
and I'm a bleeder.

11:01.226 --> 11:03.027
The key to your heart.

11:03.095 --> 11:04.996
No, that's to the Volvo.

11:06.097 --> 11:07.832
Here it is.

11:11.169 --> 11:12.269
Allow me.

11:12.337 --> 11:13.604
What are you going to do?

11:13.672 --> 11:15.339
I knew I should have
gotten the club.

11:15.406 --> 11:18.142
ZELDA:
There's the problem.

11:18.209 --> 11:20.344
Your heart is made
of valentine's candy.

11:20.412 --> 11:21.646
Oh, good.

11:21.713 --> 11:24.315
I was afraid it was going to be
something <i>serious.</i>

11:31.756 --> 11:33.590
