11:33.659 --> 11:35.192
Why is this happening to me?

11:35.260 --> 11:36.594
I eat oat bran.
(hinges squeaking)

11:36.661 --> 11:38.095
Not a huge priority,
but you might think

11:38.162 --> 11:39.363
about getting your
hinges oiled.

11:39.431 --> 11:41.231
Well, Roland, don't
just stand there

11:41.299 --> 11:42.632
fingering your
tunic; help her.

11:42.667 --> 11:45.102
I'll see what I can
find in the magic book.

11:45.170 --> 11:47.037
I remember this
from the training manual.

11:47.105 --> 11:48.638
Your condition is very serious.

11:48.706 --> 11:50.842
You must follow
my instructions precisely.

11:50.909 --> 11:52.210
What do I have to do?

11:52.277 --> 11:53.144
First, take my hand.

11:53.211 --> 11:54.612
Then what?

11:54.679 --> 11:55.646
Be patient.

11:55.714 --> 11:58.182
(humming)

11:58.249 --> 11:59.583
Is this supposed
to make me feel better?

11:59.651 --> 12:01.451
I don't know about you,
but I'm in heaven.

12:01.519 --> 12:02.887
Get out.

12:02.955 --> 12:05.055
What do you want from me?
I'm just a temp.

12:05.123 --> 12:06.757
These wings
aren't even real.

12:08.159 --> 12:09.694
Here it is.

12:09.728 --> 12:11.862
Candy heart syndrome.

12:11.930 --> 12:13.931
Well, Roland was right
about one thing.

12:13.999 --> 12:15.733
Your condition
is quite serious.

12:15.801 --> 12:17.935
"A witch gets it
only around Valentine's Day

12:18.002 --> 12:20.304
when two mortals are vying
for her heart."

12:20.371 --> 12:21.672
Two? What two?

12:21.740 --> 12:23.674
Harvey's the only one vying
for my heart--

12:23.742 --> 12:25.676
well, at least
before it was chewable.

12:25.744 --> 12:26.743
There must be someone else.

12:26.811 --> 12:28.612
Hilda, I'm so sorry...

12:28.680 --> 12:31.983
but this means that, that
valentine wasn't for you.

12:32.050 --> 12:33.483
It was for Sabrina.

12:33.551 --> 12:36.153
(deadpan voice):
Oh, no. I'm crushed.
I can't go on.

12:36.221 --> 12:39.590
Smirk, though your heart
is breaking.

12:39.658 --> 12:41.225
Oh, yeah, you know,
Aunt Hilda's problem's

12:41.293 --> 12:43.794
a lot more monumental than
the girl with the candy heart.

12:43.862 --> 12:45.129
Yeah. It's true.
Sabrina's right.

12:45.196 --> 12:47.865
We have to focus all of our
attention and support on her.

12:47.932 --> 12:48.999
All of it.

12:49.067 --> 12:50.534
SALEM:
Help! Emergency!

12:50.602 --> 12:51.602
Come quick!

12:51.669 --> 12:52.803
Be right back.

12:52.871 --> 12:54.572
It did sound dire.

12:54.639 --> 12:57.374
Well, no one can say
they coddle me.

12:57.442 --> 12:59.543
(sobbing)

12:59.610 --> 13:01.545
Salem, what's
the matter?

13:01.613 --> 13:03.647
I killed him.

13:03.715 --> 13:06.450
I landed on him
when I fell out of the tree.

13:06.518 --> 13:08.519
All I wanted to do was
scare, humiliate

13:08.587 --> 13:10.454
and emotionally scar him
for life.

13:10.522 --> 13:12.189
I didn't want to hurt him.

13:13.091 --> 13:14.825
He's still breathing.

13:14.893 --> 13:16.994
Do birdie CPR-- stat.

13:17.062 --> 13:19.563
One, two, three, four, five.

13:19.630 --> 13:20.798
Breathe.

13:20.866 --> 13:21.465
(sighs)

13:21.533 --> 13:22.900
Sorry to keep harping

13:22.968 --> 13:24.268
about this, but...

13:24.335 --> 13:25.837
it says in this book
that my symptoms are going

13:25.904 --> 13:28.339
to get progressively worse
over the next couple of hours.

13:28.406 --> 13:29.706
How can they get any worse?

13:29.774 --> 13:31.208
(heart beating loudly)

13:31.275 --> 13:33.344
Well, that's one way.

13:33.411 --> 13:36.981
Do you think anyone will believe
I have a live ferret in my bra?

13:37.048 --> 13:38.548
He's alive!
(bird chirping)

13:38.616 --> 13:40.417
Thank you, big guy.

13:40.485 --> 13:42.686
Okay, next crisis.

13:42.754 --> 13:45.189
Sabrina, you've got to stop
one of those mortals

13:45.256 --> 13:46.624
from vying for your heart.

13:46.692 --> 13:49.059
If you don't, you'll become
cold and heartless

13:49.127 --> 13:50.327
and unable to love anyone.

13:50.395 --> 13:51.561
Not even Harvey.

13:51.629 --> 13:52.596
What? But how can I get

13:52.664 --> 13:54.498
a complete stranger
to stop liking me?

13:54.566 --> 13:57.401
I know, I got to figure out
who sent me that valentine.

13:57.469 --> 13:58.970
I have an idea.

13:59.037 --> 14:01.305
We'll check out every boy
you ever met.

14:01.373 --> 14:02.740
Oh, no.
We're not going

14:02.808 --> 14:04.942
through that again.

14:05.010 --> 14:07.177
I suppose you have
a better idea.

14:07.245 --> 14:09.279
Yes, I'm calling in
a valentine expert.

14:09.347 --> 14:11.782
No!

14:11.849 --> 14:13.483
Did you not hear me say, "No!"?

14:13.551 --> 14:16.653
Well, if it isn't the girls
from ungrateful junction.

14:16.721 --> 14:18.989
Can't handle this one
without me, huh?

14:19.056 --> 14:21.158
Is there some extra
fee we can pay

14:21.226 --> 14:22.860
for you to drop
the attitude?

14:22.928 --> 14:24.495
Just tell me who sent
this valentine.

14:24.563 --> 14:27.898
Give me one good reason why
I should help you do anything.

14:27.965 --> 14:30.635
Because if you don't, your wings
will no longer be on your back

14:30.702 --> 14:33.203
but someplace
much more uncomfortable.

14:33.271 --> 14:36.173
Oh, well,
I guess we have a deal then.

14:40.044 --> 14:41.979
Old cherub party trick.

14:45.617 --> 14:46.584
Josh?

14:46.651 --> 14:48.519
Josh is my secret admirer?

14:48.587 --> 14:50.688
And he still only
pays me $5.25 an hour?

14:50.755 --> 14:52.756
Well, there's a little matter
of my fee.

14:52.824 --> 14:55.859
Sabrina, you have to
find Josh and get him

14:55.927 --> 14:57.628
to stop liking you.

14:57.695 --> 14:59.463
Unless you want to be
the kind of person who wears

14:59.531 --> 15:00.864
their heart on their sleeve,
literally.

15:00.932 --> 15:02.566
Hey, look, it stopped.

15:02.633 --> 15:04.634
I must be getting better.

15:04.702 --> 15:05.770
(music playing)

15:05.837 --> 15:07.204
I know I'm going to regret
asking this

15:07.271 --> 15:08.706
but what's that music?

15:08.773 --> 15:10.373
I think it's
Jack Benny's

15:10.441 --> 15:11.909
old theme song,
"Love In Bloom."

15:11.976 --> 15:14.612
¶ You know it isn't a dream ¶

15:14.679 --> 15:16.747
¶ It's love in bloom. ¶

15:16.814 --> 15:18.482
(imitating Benny):
Now, cut that out.

15:18.550 --> 15:21.752
Okay, so the consensus is
I'm <i>not</i> getting better.

15:21.820 --> 15:23.620
Josh, I need
to talk to you.

15:23.688 --> 15:25.422
Hey, you're back.

15:25.490 --> 15:27.224
Got that esophagus
under control?

15:27.291 --> 15:28.225
(music playing)

15:28.293 --> 15:29.527
What's with the cheesy Muzak?

15:29.594 --> 15:31.195
I thought the stereo was busted.

15:31.262 --> 15:32.897
Can I use your jacket?

15:32.931 --> 15:34.398
I'm a little chilled.

15:34.466 --> 15:37.100
I'll bring it right back.

15:37.168 --> 15:38.736
(music muffled)

15:38.804 --> 15:40.004
Okay, now it stopped.

15:40.071 --> 15:41.005
Am I going crazy?

15:41.072 --> 15:42.472
No, <i>you</i> are.

15:42.540 --> 15:44.674
What's with the jackets?

15:44.742 --> 15:46.109
Uh, kleptomania--

15:46.177 --> 15:47.978
one of my many
obnoxious qualities.

15:48.045 --> 15:50.314
You don't have
any obnoxious qualities.

15:50.348 --> 15:52.382
Sure, I do. Dozens.

15:52.450 --> 15:53.684
I can...

15:53.751 --> 15:55.119
Well, there...

15:55.186 --> 15:56.854
I can be so...

15:56.921 --> 15:57.754
Cute?

15:57.822 --> 15:59.190
Really? You think so?

15:59.257 --> 16:01.058
No, no, no, no.
No, no. Never.

16:01.126 --> 16:02.793
I am so the
opposite of cute.

16:04.562 --> 16:06.363
Curses!
Done in by my own cuteness

16:06.431 --> 16:08.198
and lack of obnoxious qualities.

16:08.266 --> 16:10.567
Well, if I can't get him
to stop liking me

16:10.635 --> 16:12.903
I'll just get him
to like someone else.

16:12.971 --> 16:15.772
Hey, um, Josh,
have you ever noticed...

16:15.840 --> 16:17.908
¶ It's love in bloom! ¶

16:19.177 --> 16:20.978
Well, well, have you?

16:21.045 --> 16:22.846
(monitor beeping rhythmically)

16:22.914 --> 16:25.282
SALEM:
Is there anything else I can do?

16:25.350 --> 16:27.017
Fluff your pillow?

16:27.085 --> 16:28.818
Regurgitate a worm?

16:28.886 --> 16:30.020
(chirping)

16:30.088 --> 16:32.489
No! No more TV for you--

16:32.557 --> 16:34.924
not since you flatlined
during <i>Popular.</i>

16:34.992 --> 16:36.827
Do you believe
in love at first sight?

16:36.895 --> 16:38.362
Maybe.

16:38.430 --> 16:40.597
Yeah, sure. I guess I'm
something of a romantic.

16:40.665 --> 16:41.598
Great.

16:41.666 --> 16:42.933
Hey, come here.

16:43.000 --> 16:44.835
What do you think?
Do you see love?

16:44.902 --> 16:47.371
No, but I do see a very
terrified customer.

16:47.439 --> 16:52.276
¶ Oh, no, it isn't the spring,
it's love in bloom. ¶

16:52.343 --> 16:53.544
Sabrina, are you okay?

16:53.611 --> 16:54.979
Yeah, fine.
Oh, what about her?

16:55.046 --> 16:56.313
She's cute.

16:56.381 --> 16:58.214
¶ It's love in bloom. ¶

16:58.282 --> 16:59.416
What's the matter with you?

16:59.484 --> 17:00.584
Why do you keep
singing that song?

17:00.652 --> 17:02.552
I'm a crazy, insane person--
the kind of person

17:02.620 --> 17:05.288
no one would ever have a secret
crush on, wouldn't you agree?

17:05.356 --> 17:06.423
Not really.

17:06.491 --> 17:08.258
But maybe you should take
the rest of the day off.

17:08.326 --> 17:10.094
Relax, get some sleep...

17:10.161 --> 17:11.528
learn a new song.

17:14.633 --> 17:17.067
The color's coming back
to his beak.

17:17.135 --> 17:18.669
The insurance companies
are right.

17:18.737 --> 17:21.571
Untrained and unqualified people
<i>can</i> treat the sick.

17:21.640 --> 17:22.439
(phone rings)

17:22.507 --> 17:23.440
Hello?

17:23.508 --> 17:24.773
SABRINA:
Hey, it's me.

17:24.842 --> 17:26.743
I just wanted to let you know
the music stopped.

17:26.810 --> 17:28.178
Oh, that's great.

17:28.246 --> 17:29.580
(bird chirping)

17:29.647 --> 17:31.215
Oh, is that stupid feather-butt
dead yet?

17:31.283 --> 17:33.450
When he finally kicks it,
make sure you flush him.

17:33.518 --> 17:36.053
Sabrina, are
you all right?

17:36.120 --> 17:37.488
Hey, watch it, buddy.

17:37.556 --> 17:39.456
Not everybody likes dogs.

17:39.524 --> 17:43.427
I swear, the blind think
the world owes them something.

17:43.495 --> 17:44.528
Something's wrong.

17:44.595 --> 17:45.929
Oh, you think?

17:45.996 --> 17:48.099
Look, I don't have time to keep
yappin' with you broads.

17:48.166 --> 17:50.167
I got to go talk to Josh;
I've been way too nice to him.

17:50.235 --> 17:51.602
I got to tell the pathetic loser

17:51.670 --> 17:54.271
that he's got to get a grip
and move on.

17:54.339 --> 17:55.906
Sabrina, wait.
(dial tone)

17:55.973 --> 17:57.408
Oh, no.

17:57.476 --> 17:59.042
Sabrina's
becoming heartless.

17:59.077 --> 18:00.711
If we don't do
something soon

18:00.778 --> 18:02.579
she'll be unable
to love anyone.

18:02.647 --> 18:05.082
We've got to get Josh
to stop liking Sabrina.

18:05.150 --> 18:07.351
I think we both know
what we have to do.

18:07.419 --> 18:08.852
If you must, you must.

18:10.788 --> 18:13.723
This is really going to cost you
this time.

18:13.791 --> 18:16.193
Hey, Juan Valdez,
we need to talk.

18:16.261 --> 18:17.828
Sabrina, how's your stomach?

18:17.896 --> 18:19.429
I brought you another kiss.

18:19.497 --> 18:21.332
Well, they never
said which boy

18:21.399 --> 18:23.000
I had to make
stop liking me.

18:23.968 --> 18:25.202
Wait, Roland,

18:25.270 --> 18:26.903
you can't go in there
dressed like that.

18:26.971 --> 18:29.372
College place...

18:29.441 --> 18:31.207
I've got just the outfit!

18:32.443 --> 18:33.844
Oh, yeah--

18:33.911 --> 18:36.513
the wings would have been
must less noticeable.

18:36.580 --> 18:37.781
Look, there's Sabrina.

18:37.816 --> 18:39.216
Oh, no.
She's with Harvey.

18:39.284 --> 18:40.884
I hope we're not too late.

18:40.952 --> 18:42.653
Wow. Sure is
an awfully long list

18:42.721 --> 18:44.721
of things you don't like
about me.

18:44.789 --> 18:46.890
Did I mention
"stating the obvious"?

18:46.958 --> 18:48.058
ZELDA:
There's Josh.

18:48.126 --> 18:49.026
Shoot him.

18:49.093 --> 18:50.694
He has to stop liking Sabrina.

18:50.762 --> 18:52.596
What-- and clear the way
for farm boy?

18:52.664 --> 18:54.197
Are you kidding?

18:54.265 --> 18:57.268
I've been waiting for Sabrina
to tell him off for years.

18:57.335 --> 18:59.002
Sabrina, what's the matter
with you?

18:59.070 --> 19:01.472
Why are you saying all this?
Don't you love me?

19:01.539 --> 19:02.839
Love? Hah!

19:02.907 --> 19:04.174
What's love?

19:04.242 --> 19:06.243
No, everything is just fine.

19:06.277 --> 19:08.445
If I can't have Sabrina,
nobody can.

19:08.512 --> 19:09.813
I don't love...

19:09.881 --> 19:11.248
I don't love...

19:11.315 --> 19:13.316
if you won't do your job,
then I will.

19:13.384 --> 19:14.718
(blowing)

19:17.655 --> 19:20.290
I don't love anyone but you.

19:21.893 --> 19:23.527
Hi. I'm Josh, Capricorn.

19:23.594 --> 19:27.197
I enjoy long walks, foreign
films and your eyes.

19:28.332 --> 19:30.501
You did that on purpose.

19:30.568 --> 19:33.037
A frivolous rebound
is exactly what you need.

19:33.104 --> 19:35.271
What I need
is to be an only child.

19:35.339 --> 19:36.840
Tell me everything
about you.

19:36.908 --> 19:38.241
Don't leave anything out.

19:38.310 --> 19:39.643
I'm already fascinated.

19:39.711 --> 19:41.444
Okay, junior.

19:41.512 --> 19:42.646
I'm so sorry.

19:42.714 --> 19:44.748
It must have been a
weird reaction to that...

19:44.815 --> 19:46.983
special sugar at my house;
can you forgive me?

19:47.051 --> 19:48.552
Of course.

19:48.620 --> 19:50.954
I knew it couldn't
really be you.

19:51.022 --> 19:54.391
You have the biggest heart
of anyone I know.

19:54.458 --> 19:56.226
ROLAND:
Hey, farm boy.

19:56.294 --> 19:57.294
Roland?!

19:57.361 --> 19:59.196
What's your cousin doing here?

19:59.263 --> 20:00.964
This.
Roland!

20:01.032 --> 20:02.700
Are you okay?

20:04.802 --> 20:06.904
Ms. Spellman,
I never realized

20:06.971 --> 20:10.541
what a devastatingly
attractive woman you are.

20:10.608 --> 20:11.608
Or that I'd ever use

20:11.676 --> 20:14.611
the word "devastatingly"
in a sentence.

20:14.679 --> 20:16.113
Happy Valentine's Day!

20:16.180 --> 20:19.383
And now it's time for
the Valentine's Day <i>massacre.</i>

20:25.623 --> 20:27.757
Oh, aurora borealis.

20:27.825 --> 20:30.894
Look at the stars, Harvey.

20:30.961 --> 20:33.763
I'd rather see them reflected
in your eyes.

20:36.200 --> 20:37.601
Come on, what are you,

20:37.668 --> 20:40.304
three, four years older
than me, tops?

20:40.371 --> 20:42.238
Try 597.

20:42.307 --> 20:43.874
Love can overcome that.

20:43.941 --> 20:45.942
Can I peel you
another grape?

20:46.010 --> 20:47.311
Whatever.

20:49.213 --> 20:52.583
Well, thank you for the worst
Valentine's Day of my life.

20:52.651 --> 20:54.418
House calls are pricey.

20:54.485 --> 20:56.052
Besides, like I told you,

20:56.120 --> 20:58.522
everything will go back
to normal after tonight.

20:58.589 --> 21:00.056
Milk Dud?

21:00.124 --> 21:02.726
(bird chirping)

21:02.794 --> 21:04.795
Sing us a song of love.

21:04.863 --> 21:06.864
Sabrina, to paraphrase

21:06.898 --> 21:09.400
the great Rod McKuen,
love is like...

21:09.467 --> 21:11.402
(yelling)

